trend_summary: Built-up cover expanded steadily, with new warehouses and offices filling former fields and forest gaps, especially west of the main arterial and near the airport. The runway/taxiway system lengthened, roads were widened, and scattered infill densified older suburbs. Tree cover shrank slightly but new landscaped patches appeared along recent estates.
notable_changes: Runway and taxiway extension at the northern airport edge.
Large industrial/warehouse parks added west of the central corridor.
Primary highway widened and new interchanges constructed.
Farmland in southwest converted to mixed commercial estates.
Incremental residential infill and greening within existing suburban blocks.
